scenarios,

00:29:06.891 --> 00:29:10.400
it's good to know that now we
know how to fend for ourselves.

00:29:10.400 --> 00:29:11.680
Personal question for you.

00:29:11.680 --> 00:29:14.210
If the apocalypse in
the way you described

00:29:14.210 --> 00:29:18.230
came, and 99.99% of the
population with decimated,

00:29:18.230 --> 00:29:21.116
beyond locking yourself up in a
supermarket for food and water

00:29:21.116 --> 00:29:22.490
for the next 55
years, what would

00:29:22.490 --> 00:29:26.230
be your personal next steps?

00:29:26.230 --> 00:29:27.310
Medicine?

00:29:27.310 --> 00:29:28.730
Go and find the biggest gun?

00:29:28.730 --> 00:29:29.360
Something else?

00:29:29.360 --> 00:29:31.850
LEWIS DARTNELL: Yeah, so
there's been a bunch of reviews

00:29:31.850 --> 00:29:34.621
on the Amazon US site,
and there's allegedly

00:29:34.621 --> 00:29:36.370
been a bunch of preppers
who have reviewed

00:29:36.370 --> 00:29:38.390
this book about
rebuilding civilization.

00:29:38.390 --> 00:29:39.854
And they just love their guns.

00:29:39.854 --> 00:29:41.270
And one of the
major questions is,

00:29:41.270 --> 00:29:43.517
you haven't talked about
weaponry in your book.

00:29:43.517 --> 00:29:44.600
And, of course, it's true.

00:29:44.600 --> 00:29:47.560
But again, the resounding bottom
line is, if you've got a gun,

00:29:47.560 --> 00:29:48.080
you're fine.

00:29:48.080 --> 00:29:49.772
If you don't have
a gun, find one.

00:29:49.772 --> 00:29:51.230
It's not an
interesting discussion.

00:29:51.230 --> 00:29:53.242
There's no interesting
answer to be had there.

00:29:53.242 --> 00:29:55.450
And the knowledge isn't
going to help you either way.

00:29:55.450 --> 00:29:58.120
So I avoided guns right
from the beginning,

00:29:58.120 --> 00:30:00.980
for the same reason I avoid
the politics and stuff.

00:30:00.980 --> 00:30:03.920
But clearly, for this
book to be relevant,

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:06.370
you have to be in a world
that isn't like "The Road."

00:30:06.370 --> 00:30:07.780
You have to be
beyond that stage.

00:30:07.780 --> 00:30:09.050
This is what happens next.

00:30:09.050 --> 00:30:11.980
And you have got some
semblance of stable society,

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:14.560
where people are now
ready to start progressing

00:30:14.560 --> 00:30:16.845
and rebuilding, as
happened in 1340s

00:30:16.845 --> 00:30:18.720
after the bubonic plague
and the Black Death.

00:30:18.720 --> 00:30:19.769
A lot of people died.

00:30:19.769 --> 00:30:21.810
People shrugged their
shoulders, stiff upper lip,

00:30:21.810 --> 00:30:24.655
and got on with it.

00:30:24.655 --> 00:30:27.355
So the next step, the
one piece of information

00:30:27.355 --> 00:30:30.770
that I think would be most
critical out of all knowledge

00:30:30.770 --> 00:30:33.370
that you would really want
to preserve and not forget,

00:30:33.370 --> 00:30:34.875
I've hinted at
already, is this idea

00:30:34.875 --> 00:30:36.650
of germ theory and hygiene.

00:30:36.650 --> 00:30:39.780
There is nothing you can do more
for yourself to keep yourself

00:30:39.780 --> 00:30:42.050
healthy and alive than
stopping yourself picking up

00:30:42.050 --> 00:30:45.090
a transmissible infection
in the first place.

00:30:45.090 --> 00:30:47.270
And the basic tenets of
germ theory and hygiene

00:30:47.270 --> 00:30:48.936
are what will really
help you out there,

00:30:48.936 --> 00:30:50.690
when there aren't
antibiotics anymore.

00:30:50.690 --> 00:30:52.520
So, we aren't
being too prurient.

00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:54.607
Make sure you're not
drinking your own excrement,

00:30:54.607 --> 00:30:56.440
making sure no one else
is putting excrement

00:30:56.440 --> 00:30:58.564
into the river where you're
taking your water from.

00:30:58.564 --> 00:31:01.530
And you laugh now, and this is
obviously a disgusting thing.

00:31:01.530 --> 00:31:03.450
As late as the
1850s, 1860s, that's

00:31:03.450 --> 00:31:06.020
what happened in London,
the capital of the most

00:31:06.020 --> 00:31:07.885
powerful empire
in the world, they

00:31:07.885 --> 00:31:09.760
were pouring their poo
into the River Thames,

00:31:09.760 --> 00:31:11.870
and someone else 20 yards
down the road, down the river,

00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:13.520
was pulling up a
bucket and drinking it.

00:31:13.520 --> 00:31:15.061
And tens of thousands
of people would

00:31:15.061 --> 00:31:17.540
be dying in a week with
cholera, but for really easily

00:31:17.540 --> 00:31:18.249
preventable ways.

00:31:18.249 --> 00:31:20.040
So one of the key
technologies I talk about

00:31:20.040 --> 00:31:22.440
is how to make a microscope,
ludicrously simple,

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:25.115
to prove to yourself that
there are these organisms, that

00:31:25.115 --> 00:31:27.490
are too small to see
that cause disease,

00:31:27.490 --> 00:31:31.165
and you want to break that
cycle with things like hygiene.

00:31:31.165 --> 00:31:34.890
It demonstrates
scientifically, with evidence,

00:31:34.890 --> 00:31:37.277
why this is important.

